summary_text: 1. I was working in the warehouse. 2. I was stocking boxes and organizing merchandise. 3. I felt lightheaded after working for a few hours. 4. I thought the lightheadedness was due to hunger. 5. I felt tightness and pressure in my chest. 6. I leaned against a wall to rest. 7. The pressure in my chest got stronger. 8. I felt my heart pounding. 9. I started seeing spots and sweating. 10. I couldn't catch my breath. 11. I heard the manager's voice across the warehouse. 12. The manager checked if I was alright. 13. I couldn't yell back or find my voice. 14. The manager walked towards me. 15. I started to drop to the ground. 16. The manager caught me before I fell. 17. The manager took me to the staff room. 18. The manager asked what was wrong and got me water. 19. I realized I had a panic attack. 20. I learned to check in with myself to prevent episodes.
